containers available in c++98:
    vector
    map
    list     : doubly-linked list 
    deque    : double-ended queue
    set      : collection of unique keys, sorted by keys
    multiset : collection of keys, sorted by keys 
    multimap : collection of key-value pairs, sorted by keys 

container adapters: they provide a different interface for sequential containers:
    stack           : adapts a container to provide stack (LIFO data structure) (uses deque by default)
    queue           : adapts a container to provide queue (FIFO data structure)
    priority_queue  : adapts a container to provide priority queue (uses vector)



